-MiNhctRogxVxDjp5HLa.text: An update from the Saint Paul Police Department Twitter page states police are investigating after a woman's body was recovered in her apartment.

-MiOD3IoJS8kzd98Gaa0.text: Saint Paul Police are treating the woman's death as a homicide.

nib.text:
Homicide detectives are investigating a suspicious death in Summit Hill after a woman’s body was found in her condo Monday morning.

The woman, who was in her 50s, was found dead by her family, according to a statement from the Saint Paul Police Department.

The family called the police. Officers arrived at the 300 block of Ramsey Street shortly before 11 a.m. 

Police brought in the county medical examiner, who found the death suspicious.

Forensics experts are gathering evidence on scene. Homicide investigators are interviewing people and looking for witnesses.

Citizen user video showed first responders outside the residence with the area taped off.

An autopsy will determine the exact cause of death.

No arrests had been made as of Monday evening.

Police called the death Saint Paul's 22nd homicide in 2021. It's the fourth since early Sunday morning.

results.rawLocation: 7th St E & Mounds Blvd, Saint Paul, Minnesota, 55106
results.title: Fatal Shooting Investigation

-MiJoI_kbbBHi7ixQeTq.text: Citizen user sumoshouldntbeher shows a large police presence at an incident.

-MiK26Msox4bCSNSRW10.text: The address reported for this incident has changed to 7th St E & Mounds Blvd.

-MiK26V6sXL0oGFpQXWn.text: According to a tweet from the St Paul Police Department, police are investigating the fatal shooting that occurred earlier in the evening. No suspect information is available.

-MiKTBX04FvARkrr2eS9.text: According to a press release from the St Paul Police Department, police received a 911 call for shots fired around 8:45 pm. Officers responded to the scene at 7 St E and Mounds Blvd where they found a man believed to be in his late teens inside a vehicle. He was unconscious, but breathing and suffering from gunshot wounds. Police rendered aid to the man while they secured the scene. EMS transported the man to a local hospital where he was pronounced deceased a short time later. Investigators from the homicide unit are working to locate possible witnesses who can help them identify the person or people responsible for the death. Members of the forensic services unit will process the scene and the area for evidence, and the video management unit will work to locate surveillance video. Preliminary information indicates this shooting may be connected to a road rage incident, however it’s unclear how the victim was involved. No arrests have been made. Anyone with information about this shooting is asked to call the homicide unit at 651-266-5650.
